Business Brief -- Highland Superstores Inc.:
   Retailer Plans to Reduce
   Work Force by About 500
"The streamlining of our work force and operations, both
in our stores, and in our corporate offices, is designed to
enable Highland to become an even lower-cost operator,"
Highland President Ira Mondry said in a prepared statement.
   Highland, which already has pulled out of several markets,
has no plans to close any of its 49 remaining stores in
Michigan, Ohio, Indiana and Illinois, he added.